{{liushu|p}} – a person with the hands held behind the back, possibly the original character for {{m|zh|逡巡}}.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs *''winʔ'' or *''junʔ'':
* If *''junʔ'', then possibly related to {{cog|my|ယုံ||to believe}}; if so, from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*yum||to believe}}; other cognates would then be {{cog|csh|yón-é}}, {{cog|mrh|zó}}, {{cog|lhu|ʑo³¹}}.
* If *''winʔ'', then {{och-l|信}} (minimally reconstructed *''sin(s)'') is its possible derivative.

